# implementation_plan.md - Adding Settings Menu and Theme Support

This plan details the addition of a floating settings menu to the surgery schedule page, enabling auto-refresh and theme customization.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component] UI/UX & Themes Refinement

#### [MODIFY] [legacy_schedule.html](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/Combined_Server/SurgerySchedule/templates/legacy_schedule.html)

- **Global Variable Cleanup**:
    - Ensure all components (Assessment, Details, Table) use `var(--text)`, `var(--bg)`, `var(--card)`, and `var(--border)`.
    - Handle `.h2-container`, `.h3-header`, `.h3-content` styles.

- **Surgery Card Visibility**:
    - Add `border: 1px solid var(--border)` to `.surgery-card`.
    - In `.theme-dark`, ensure `--border` is light enough (e.g., `#444`) to be visible against the background.

- **Modal & Overlay Support**:
    - Ensure `#detail-view` and `#eval-modal-content` correctly inherit theme backgrounds.
    - Update `data-table` and `sub-list` borders to use CSS variables.

